9a2c7e49-719a-5e74-aa54-9d202d5d55c2.title: Common registers and commands

Their code is listed as say `@ intensity` and not `@ 0x01` (the spectool enforces that).

It also introduces capacitive touch sensing, a power-saving mode and more computing power for the classroom.

2a7e95b4-72fc-579c-8549-a961e62b4249.description: Accelerometer sensors are devices used to measure acceleration or motion.

c1c5e586-350f-5610-93c1-b441a7c2283d.description: A sensor measuring water acidity, commonly called pH.

7c139374-de3c-505e-b5ab-5be44eea8c75.description: This is the first mechanical keyboard in the Jacdac system, featuring a 60% layout, a rotary encoder, RGB LED lighting, and two Jacdac interfaces. It is powered by the RP2040 microcontroller.

a42ee426-4b8c-5156-8cf0-9db3554e5a86.title: Air Pressure
a42ee426-4b8c-5156-8cf0-9db3554e5a86.description: A sensor measuring air pressure of outside environment.

0031b9d7-da2c-5759-962c-8c93fad11377.title: AgileWhisker Numeric Keypad
0031b9d7-da2c-5759-962c-8c93fad11377.description: This is the first numeric keypad in the Jacdac system, featuring an OLED screen, a rotary encoder, RGB LED lighting, and one Jacdac interface. It is powered by the RP2040 microcontroller.

dc5ad79f-2783-587f-a00a-01f6da6ce37d.title: Air Quality Index
dc5ad79f-2783-587f-a00a-01f6da6ce37d.description:
The Air Quality Index is a measure of how clean or polluted air is. From min, good quality, to high, low quality.
The range of AQI may vary between countries (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_quality_index).

46a4cb9c-e2ca-55db-bd10-6d3ee886de65.title: AW Agent
46a4cb9c-e2ca-55db-bd10-6d3ee886de65.description: AW Agent, short for AgileWhisker Agent, is a small software for PC computers that is designed to be used in conjunction with AgileWhisker Keyboard Elite60 and other keyboards. It is an open-source software. It functions as a virtual hardware within the jacdac ecosystem. It incorporates MQTT services to retrieve hardware information from the computer and trigger computer events, among other functionalities.

1a57487e-8b83-5a7c-ab66-6ad56ef454df.description:
This service is deprecated in favor of `gamepad` (although it is currently used by the micro:bit Arcade smart shield).
A gamepad with direction and action buttons for one player.
If a device has multiple controllers, it should have multiple gamepad services, using consecutive service identifiers.

7dc7669a-95e7-506c-b9d9-71c0a6206981.title: DuckyBot Kit
7dc7669a-95e7-506c-b9d9-71c0a6206981.description: Dive into the enchanting world of robotics with DuckyBot, a delightful cardboard robot shaped like a cheerful yellow duck. Engineered around the groundbreaking Jacdac Elite Module Suite, DuckyBot offers young learners a quirky and entertaining gateway into the vast realm of electronics and robotics, integrating seamlessly with Microbit and Makecode platforms.

fe8345ca-b298-56fa-8175-3c449162aa37.title: Arcade Sound
fe8345ca-b298-56fa-8175-3c449162aa37.description:
A sound playing device.

This is typically run over an SPI connection, not regular single-wire Jacdac.

62bd4420-136a-5ac2-b422-49b741f05779.title: Env Sensor
62bd4420-136a-5ac2-b422-49b741f05779.description: Env Sensor is a device used to measure both the temperature and humidity of the surrounding environment.

16e5a6f1-6dd9-5e85-bf31-d1bee618c924.title: Barcode reader
16e5a6f1-6dd9-5e85-bf31-d1bee618c924.description: A device that reads various barcodes, like QR codes. For the web, see [BarcodeDetector](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/BarcodeDetector).

c6bbc2c1-4956-5d37-83b8-54df82e25863.title: Grape:bit
c6bbc2c1-4956-5d37-83b8-54df82e25863.description: Grape:bit is a programming main control board mainly for the second to third grade information technology learning and institutional teaching. Its core is the ESP32, which has the characteristics of high performance, wireless communication, and graphical programming.

94a7d4cd-39d3-5f47-8548-b7e23852d9ab.title: bit:radio
94a7d4cd-39d3-5f47-8548-b7e23852d9ab.description: Support for sending and receiving packets using the [Bit Radio protocol](https://github.com/microsoft/pxt-common-packages/blob/master/libs/radio/docs/reference/radio.md), typically used between micro:bit devices.

d3cf0f64-4c73-5dc5-8157-20338d878834.title: Haptic Output
d3cf0f64-4c73-5dc5-8157-20338d878834.description: The Haptic Output module is essentially a vibration motor that can be used to provide haptic feedback in electronic devices.

7c87e711-d449-557d-aec4-4c6f640b9028.title: Bootloader
7c87e711-d449-557d-aec4-4c6f640b9028.description:
Allows flashing (reprogramming) devices over Jacdac.

This is typically implemented by having a separate _bootloader_ mode, as opposed to _application_ mode
on the module to be flashed.
The bootloader mode is entered on every device reset, for about 300ms.
The bootloader will generally not announce itself, until it gets some command.
Once it gets the command, it will stay in application mode.

Typically, you ask the module (in application mode) to reset, while sending broadcast
`info` commands to all bootloaders every 100ms or so.
Alternatively, you ask the the user to disconnect and re-connect the module, while
broadcasting `info` commands.
The second method works even if the application is damaged (eg., due to an aborted flash).

When device is in bootloader mode, the device ID may change compared to application mode,
by flipping the first bit in the first byte of the device identifier.

c3f53d74-77f8-5c0c-af74-bf458c93fcbc.title: Braille display
c3f53d74-77f8-5c0c-af74-bf458c93fcbc.description: A Braille pattern display module. This module display [unicode braille patterns](https://www.unicode.org/charts/PDF/U2800.pdf), country specific encoding have to be implemented by the clients.

It Includes:

Jacdac-RGB Strip	X1
Jacdac-Servo	X1
Jacdac-Ultrasonic	X1
Jacdac-Hub_B	X1
Jacdac Cable  10 cm	X2
Jacdac Cable 35 cm	X2
Jacdac Cable  100 cm	X1

1d8fc87d-12f3-56ba-8763-914cabf4335a.title: Bridge
1d8fc87d-12f3-56ba-8763-914cabf4335a.description: Indicates that the device acts as a bridge to the Jacdac bus.

0f826e4c-7a03-58da-901d-97ee83902ae7.title: Jacdac Starter Kit A with Jacdaptor for micro:bit V2

e3f3ed97-54aa-508f-b845-b741bdc70578.title: Button
e3f3ed97-54aa-508f-b845-b741bdc70578.description: A push-button, which returns to inactive position when not operated anymore.

88b5ae02-7352-56da-9b38-b8971ed46c22.title: Capacitive Button
88b5ae02-7352-56da-9b38-b8971ed46c22.description: A configuration service for a capacitive push-button.

8d9dfd96-46f6-5e7d-b80a-06b74ef11c9b.title: Character Screen
8d9dfd96-46f6-5e7d-b80a-06b74ef11c9b.description: A screen that displays characters, typically a LCD/OLED character screen.

1961da73-5473-55ae-9ea6-afd5524b9550.title: Cloud Adapter
1961da73-5473-55ae-9ea6-afd5524b9550.description:
Supports cloud connections to upload and download data.
Note that `f64` values following a label are not necessarily aligned.

26d3f9d6-cc0b-5899-95b4-08304e2aa559.title: NanoScript 2040
26d3f9d6-cc0b-5899-95b4-08304e2aa559.description: Elevate your embedded projects with our cutting-edge development board, powered by Raspberry Pi's RP2040 and tailored for DeviceScript. Experience the unmatched synergy of TypeScript in the realm of microcontroller programming, where precision, efficiency, and modern development practices converge.

1f3f861e-20b7-5909-936b-1db43ddce403.title: Cloud Configuration
1f3f861e-20b7-5909-936b-1db43ddce403.description: Connection and diagnostics information about the cloud connection.

e12239d4-f0fd-58d5-82b0-d520f4005d77.title: Newbit Arcade Shield Expansion Board for Micro:bit V2
e12239d4-f0fd-58d5-82b0-d520f4005d77.description: KittenBot Newbit Arcade Shield is an expansion board developed exclusively for Micro:bit V2. It provides Micro:bit V2 the ability not only to be a console, but also to create programmable games. Equipped with the Newbit Arcade Shield, you can use Micro:bit to design games online in MakeCodeArcade, or play games offline, which will broaden your experience of programming with Micro:bit V2.

2077a73d-fe61-57e4-a9bf-45a06319b383.title: CODAL Message Bus
2077a73d-fe61-57e4-a9bf-45a06319b383.description:
A service that uses the [CODAL message bus](https://lancaster-university.github.io/microbit-docs/ubit/messageBus/) to send and receive small messages.

You can find known values for `source` in [CODAL repository](https://github.com/lancaster-university/codal-core/blob/master/inc/core/CodalComponent.h)
In MakeCode, you can listen for custom `source`, `value` values using [control.onEvent](https://makecode.microbit.org/reference/control/on-event].

976dea58-4d46-5571-bbc8-93f990c98eed.title: Power
976dea58-4d46-5571-bbc8-93f990c98eed.description: Power module is used to supply high-current JACDAC modules such as servo modules.It can also be used to supply power to the entire JACDAC electronic system.It has overcurrent protection and a maximum output current of 1A.

4c10fea8-c7dc-543e-898c-45f70a5ad6e9.title: Relay
4c10fea8-c7dc-543e-898c-45f70a5ad6e9.description:
This relay module is designed for low voltage and low current applications. It's recommended to use a voltage of 5V and a current no greater than 1A.
When using a relay module, it's important to be aware of electrical safety. It's recommended that you use the relay module under adult supervision, especially if you are not familiar with electrical circuits and how to use them safely.

509bc146-7a0d-5665-9fd5-6bbb399e3af3.title: Compass
509bc146-7a0d-5665-9fd5-6bbb399e3af3.description: A sensor that measures the heading.

f80f5cdb-1769-5ca2-91c0-f10b1c4b35ad.title: RGB Ring
f80f5cdb-1769-5ca2-91c0-f10b1c4b35ad.description: A ring of 8 colored programmable LEDs.

e4ce419b-b66c-548e-996f-e91a0c44a3a0.title: Control
e4ce419b-b66c-548e-996f-e91a0c44a3a0.description:
Control service is always service index `0`.
It handles actions common to all services on a device.

Note: some of the optional features (including `flood_ping`, `mcu_temperature`, and all string registers)
are not implemented in `8bit` version.

ef791dfd-1583-55d2-a4e7-4b67ae4e796f.title: RGB Strip
ef791dfd-1583-55d2-a4e7-4b67ae4e796f.description: RGB Strip module is used to drive WS2812 LED strips. If you're driving a large number of LEDs, such as more than 10, it's recommended to provide additional power to the LED strip to ensure stable and reliable operation.

4905ee7e-d863-5b2f-b496-4cc9651c3436.title: Dashboard
4905ee7e-d863-5b2f-b496-4cc9651c3436.description: Device that interacts, configure or inspects with the services on the bus. While a dashboard is on the bus, heuristics like device reset should be disabled.

ee9f5981-143d-5cd7-9ab1-2262062b61a6.title: DC Current Measurement
ee9f5981-143d-5cd7-9ab1-2262062b61a6.description: A service that reports a current measurement.

45f07701-d082-5a82-bd37-fdf3bed06834.title: Servo
45f07701-d082-5a82-bd37-fdf3bed06834.description: Servo module is used to drive standard 3-wire analog servos. It has two output channels and can operate in two different current output modes: 500mA and 1A.

cac12bac-c885-5535-a765-73d6675f9856.title: DC Voltage Measurement
cac12bac-c885-5535-a765-73d6675f9856.description: A service that reports a voltage measurement.

f12be37f-20f8-543d-9b14-e9dacaaa3800.description:
Conditions are synthetic services used to synchronize threads of executions of a DeviceScript VM.
**This is no longer used**.

e8f79697-44d2-5969-9117-4a5ab4509a20.title: Ultrasonic Sensor
e8f79697-44d2-5969-9117-4a5ab4509a20.description: The Ultrasonic Distance Measurement module has a detection range of approximately 3.5 meters.

d2ff59e3-0e1f-57ed-8d7c-5090e6833f70.title: DeviceScript Debugger
d2ff59e3-0e1f-57ed-8d7c-5090e6833f70.description: Allows for inspecting and affecting the state of a running DeviceScript program.

f3e9712a-6186-5351-817f-28605e908db8.title: Game:bit Expansion Board
f3e9712a-6186-5351-817f-28605e908db8.description: Game:Bit is a brand new product based on Microsoft Arcade games , providing users with different choices for learning micro:bit. Break away from the previous model of using expansion boards and sensors to create projects, and use the method of creating interesting games to stimulate learners' different programming thinking. From how to set the scoring method, character movements, background and music matching, to the judgment of victory and defeat and the ending process, everything in the entire game is decided by the game creator.

0e09030e-6a21-585d-a24a-3610c5b9f1d5.title: DeviceScript Manager
0e09030e-6a21-585d-a24a-3610c5b9f1d5.description:
Allows for deployment and control over DeviceScript virtual machine.

Programs start automatically after device restart or uploading of new program.
You can stop programs until next reset by setting the `running` and `autostart` registers to `false`.

acc8fc99-f95e-5396-b31f-c36acf69ba7a.title: Distance
acc8fc99-f95e-5396-b31f-c36acf69ba7a.description: A sensor that determines the distance of an object without any physical contact involved.

10f339ba-6483-5552-b778-5b490a7c9ee7.title: Climate Action Kit
10f339ba-6483-5552-b778-5b490a7c9ee7.description: Purpose-driven STEM education for a brighter future.  Explore climate action with our STEM kit and online lessons.

70f30020-e43c-5e14-bd63-68cb9d96ed12.title: DMX
70f30020-e43c-5e14-bd63-68cb9d96ed12.description: A service that can send DMX512-A packets with limited size. This service is designed to allow tinkering with a few DMX devices, but only allows 235 channels. More about DMX at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DMX512.

924861ec-9906-52f6-ab5b-31fccb660894.title: Dial Button
924861ec-9906-52f6-ab5b-31fccb660894.description: Dial Button is a rotary encoder and button compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

1e2dc157-b9ad-5899-8a0a-acccef15b371.title: Dot Matrix
1e2dc157-b9ad-5899-8a0a-acccef15b371.description: A rectangular dot matrix display, made of monochrome LEDs or Braille pins.

7be7179c-4a27-5a0b-9bdb-8a6cf492dd85.title: Float Sensor
7be7179c-4a27-5a0b-9bdb-8a6cf492dd85.description: This Forward Education Jacdac sensor monitors when water reaches a specific level. It uses a simple internal float that activates a signal at a set water height. Your project reads this signal through the Jacdac connection to know the level status.

97e5a0d0-8772-5fc9-bbd6-5b7f7a33db7c.title: Learn to Solder Kit
97e5a0d0-8772-5fc9-bbd6-5b7f7a33db7c.description: Learn to solder by assembling this module's through-hole components yourself. Once built, you'll have a device with 3 LEDs and 3 buttons that can be quickly integrated with your Jacdac projects via code, or powered standalone using a coin cell battery.

28ca6b5e-6e80-532f-81e8-47151c353d14.title: LED Lights
28ca6b5e-6e80-532f-81e8-47151c353d14.description: LED Lights is a ws2812 LED ring compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

911437f7-3056-5ab5-8799-2cff01d6717a.title: Lights
911437f7-3056-5ab5-8799-2cff01d6717a.description: Control dimmable LED light strips with the Forward Education Jacdac "Lights" module.  It uses an external 5V or 12V power supply to safely power and manage brightness levels for your LEDs.  Integrate and command your lighting easily through the standard Jacdac connection.

41ee6183-7a1c-5601-a4f5-45242b858f9c.title: Gamepad
41ee6183-7a1c-5601-a4f5-45242b858f9c.description: A two axis directional gamepad with optional buttons.

3904daf0-0a75-5c9a-8d5c-b64192be1551.title: Line Sensor
3904daf0-0a75-5c9a-8d5c-b64192be1551.description: Line Sensor is a multi-reflected light sensor compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

b4e40075-f62c-5f2a-905e-7019edf3535c.title: GPIO
b4e40075-f62c-5f2a-905e-7019edf3535c.description:
Access to General Purpose Input/Output (GPIO) pins on a board.
The pins are indexed `0 ... num_pins-1`.
The indexing does not correspond to hardware pin names, nor labels on the board (see `get_pin_info` command for that),
and should **not** be exposed to the user.

ab58fde1-5030-5f3a-a4a2-04e567d41c5d.title: Moisture Sensor
ab58fde1-5030-5f3a-a4a2-04e567d41c5d.description: Moisture Sensor is a capacitive soil moisture sensor compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

2c6fc31f-ae10-56d7-9b03-31346ab8a2b3.title: pH Sensor
2c6fc31f-ae10-56d7-9b03-31346ab8a2b3.description: pH Sensor is a sensor module and probe compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the sensor module ecosystem by Forward Education

d9517b76-a072-5d5b-be75-f246d9dbf769.title: Heart Rate
d9517b76-a072-5d5b-be75-f246d9dbf769.description:
A sensor approximating the heart rate. 


**Jacdac is NOT suitable for medical devices and should NOT be used in any kind of device to diagnose or treat any medical conditions.**

8c3deeab-0749-5302-88c3-550eb8452732.title: Solar Sensor
8c3deeab-0749-5302-88c3-550eb8452732.description: Solar Sensor is a photoresistor sensor compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

b5127708-8db7-575f-ba92-f55a214f9002.title: Sonar Sensor
b5127708-8db7-575f-ba92-f55a214f9002.description: Sonar Sensor is an ultrasonic/radar sensor compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

4f314937-8f9d-5d0f-a1f5-4c4b486d9fe4.title: HID Keyboard
4f314937-8f9d-5d0f-a1f5-4c4b486d9fe4.description:
Control a HID keyboard.

The codes for the key (selectors) is defined in the [HID Keyboard
specification](https://usb.org/sites/default/files/hut1_21.pdf), chapter 10 Keyboard/Keypad Page, page 81.
Modifiers are in page 87.

The device keeps tracks of the key state and is able to clear it all with the clear command.

a8b043e1-5117-5bdd-9d27-a847d7f7b602.title: Temperature Probe
a8b043e1-5117-5bdd-9d27-a847d7f7b602.description: Measure temperature precisely with the Forward Education Jacdac Temperature Sensor.  This module utilizes a digital DS18B20 sensor for reliable and accurate readings.  Connect instantly via Jacdac to bring temperature data into your projects.

42148aa2-1d8a-54a6-bd7d-c97c303a677e.title: Touch Sensor
42148aa2-1d8a-54a6-bd7d-c97c303a677e.description: Touch Sensor is a capacitive touch sensor compatible with the jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

b889c9d1-d6f8-58cb-8c73-e50eb3651b59.title: Humidity
b889c9d1-d6f8-58cb-8c73-e50eb3651b59.description: A sensor measuring humidity of outside environment.

f56b9647-3472-5521-b521-2b859d1fdb5b.title: I2C
f56b9647-3472-5521-b521-2b859d1fdb5b.description:
Inter-Integrated Circuit (I2C, I²C, IIC) serial communication bus lets you communicate with
many sensors and actuators.

7d7020f5-12b2-5c30-b7ea-0dd89ea5512a.title: Jacdac:bit
7d7020f5-12b2-5c30-b7ea-0dd89ea5512a.description: Jacdac:bit is a micro:bit interface module for easy connection to Jacdac devices, ideal for learning and interactive projects.

a154d921-3669-54aa-a5f1-76c0136caaa0.title: Illuminance
a154d921-3669-54aa-a5f1-76c0136caaa0.description:
Detects the amount of light falling onto a given surface area.

Note that this is different from _luminance_, the amount of light that passes through, emits from, or reflects off an object.

55014d55-d8d3-5a91-b7e4-89a26b33a7ea.title: Indexed screen
55014d55-d8d3-5a91-b7e4-89a26b33a7ea.description:
A screen with indexed colors from a palette.

This is often run over an SPI connection or directly on the MCU, not regular single-wire Jacdac.

26f98c9b-0f9d-5f96-ab38-f150a496f0d6.title: Infrastructure
26f98c9b-0f9d-5f96-ab38-f150a496f0d6.description:
A service that tags a device as purely infrastructure device.


A Jacdac user interface can hide any device that hosts this service.

4ebcebba-eeb5-5715-a5ae-89c7446837ca.title: LED
4ebcebba-eeb5-5715-a5ae-89c7446837ca.description:
A controller for displays of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

For 64 or less LEDs, the service should support the pack the pixels in the pixels register.
Beyond this size, the register should return an empty payload as the amount of data exceeds
the size of a packet. Typically services that use more than 64 LEDs
will run on the same MCU and will maintain the pixels buffer internally.

df9d106e-354d-567d-b423-2a5bc379a430.title: LED Single
df9d106e-354d-567d-b423-2a5bc379a430.description: A controller for 1 or more monochrome or RGB LEDs connected in parallel.

2c300a04-840b-598b-9643-fb43c8c41e5c.title: LED Strip
2c300a04-840b-598b-9643-fb43c8c41e5c.description: A controller for strips of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

bf4dab54-38a5-5c2a-8116-bad40075f2b0.title: Light level
bf4dab54-38a5-5c2a-8116-bad40075f2b0.description: A sensor that measures luminosity level.

bc6f2314-706a-5329-b03b-52d7a4b7c4be.title: Logger
bc6f2314-706a-5329-b03b-52d7a4b7c4be.description: A service which can report messages to the bus.

0253b1f4-9a63-5e07-963b-80c0851708d4.title: Magnetic field level
0253b1f4-9a63-5e07-963b-80c0851708d4.description: A sensor that measures strength and polarity of magnetic field.

47e09f1c-3dff-5bcb-aa4d-b2bb7fd7a1b9.title: micro:bit Retro Programming Arcade
47e09f1c-3dff-5bcb-aa4d-b2bb7fd7a1b9.description: micro:bit Retro Arcade is a color screen joystick expansion board for micro:bit V2, it contains a TFT 160*128 color screen, 4 directional buttons, two A/B buttons and a reset button. micro:bit Retro Arcade can be used with micro:bit V2 to program games online and play offline on the Microsoft Arcade programming platform. It is a simple and fun way to help children write their own games and understand the mystery behind them. It also supports custom game characters, diverse scenarios and plot design using graphical programming software, making it easy for everyone to achieve fun electronic creations and unlimited game ideas. micro:bit Retro Arcade can also be used as a remote control handle in addition to a game programming learning machine.

de8725e9-aac8-5c3d-ac4b-7740731131e2.title: Matrix Keypad
de8725e9-aac8-5c3d-ac4b-7740731131e2.description: A matrix of buttons connected as a keypad

368b6875-86b3-5dc9-9985-1d07cd6dc927.title: Calliope mini V3
368b6875-86b3-5dc9-9985-1d07cd6dc927.description: Calliope mini is an easy-to-program microcontroller that has quite a few internal sensors and, in addition to a pin header and two Grove connectors it also features two JacDac connectors to connect sensors and actuators directly to the board.

ec0897b0-734c-54ec-8430-ada114d91af1.title: JM Base
ec0897b0-734c-54ec-8430-ada114d91af1.description: A breadboard like PCB to screw mount Jacdac modules.

735bf89a-945a-5b0b-9373-57ee732ab07e.title: Model Runner
735bf89a-945a-5b0b-9373-57ee732ab07e.description:
Runs machine learning models.

Only models with a single input tensor and a single output tensor are supported at the moment.
Input is provided by Sensor Aggregator service on the same device.
Multiple instances of this service may be present, if more than one model format is supported by a device.

c7d41c1f-5998-5ae5-b46a-d9ac9f2fa098.title: Motion
c7d41c1f-5998-5ae5-b46a-d9ac9f2fa098.description: A sensor, typically PIR, that detects object motion within a certain range

85aebf60-8a6e-5e64-b5d4-caf3b6c3675c.title: Multitouch
85aebf60-8a6e-5e64-b5d4-caf3b6c3675c.description: A capacitive touch sensor with multiple inputs.

9f6007fe-ca85-523d-b949-70d8480867d6.title: PC controller
9f6007fe-ca85-523d-b949-70d8480867d6.description: Send various events to PC, including opening a URL, start an app, sending text, etc.

41b55b31-622d-559a-b74a-f01b0b50c242.title: Planar position
41b55b31-622d-559a-b74a-f01b0b50c242.description:
A sensor that repors 2D position, typically an optical mouse tracking sensor.

The sensor starts at an arbitrary origin (0,0) and reports the distance from that origin.

The `streaming_interval` is respected when the position is changing. When the position is not changing, the streaming interval may be throttled to `500ms`.

8e35e21d-f799-5a2d-b6ff-c3ddf2ca22a5.title: Power supply
8e35e21d-f799-5a2d-b6ff-c3ddf2ca22a5.description: A power supply with a fixed or variable voltage range

da58aa28-7e6c-57db-836e-4e8596f0e52b.title: Protocol Test
da58aa28-7e6c-57db-836e-4e8596f0e52b.description:
This is test service to validate the protocol packet transmissions between the browser and a MCU.
Use this page if you are porting Jacdac to a new platform.

0ca81209-eae6-5f58-b354-684c4e676db5.title: Proxy
0ca81209-eae6-5f58-b354-684c4e676db5.description:
A service that tags a device as a packet proxy.
A device in proxy mode will proxy Jacdac packets and typically has its core logic halted.

f7718794-9e72-5649-9541-ff5d1cdd435a.title: Pulse Oximeter
f7718794-9e72-5649-9541-ff5d1cdd435a.description:
A sensor approximating the oxygen level.

**Jacdac is not suitable for medical devices and should NOT be used in any kind of device to diagnose or treat any medical conditions.**

bd44d935-403c-5e58-8800-9060d75003a7.title: Rain gauge
bd44d935-403c-5e58-8800-9060d75003a7.description: Measures the amount of liquid precipitation over an area in a predefined period of time.

498a541f-ed21-5f2a-ad0d-98f505a05687.title: Real time clock
498a541f-ed21-5f2a-ad0d-98f505a05687.description: Real time clock to support collecting data with precise time stamps.

96c22b44-6b7f-557a-b49c-09ce4a96ed6d.title: Reflected light
96c22b44-6b7f-557a-b49c-09ce4a96ed6d.description: A sensor that detects light and dark surfaces, commonly used for line following robots.

98a1021b-f50a-5a36-bc26-3e124e0c29e5.title: Relay
98a1021b-f50a-5a36-bc26-3e124e0c29e5.description:
A switching relay.

The contacts should be labelled `NO` (normally open), `COM` (common), and `NC` (normally closed).
When relay is energized it connects `NO` and `COM`.
When relay is not energized it connects `NC` and `COM`.
Some relays may be missing `NO` or `NC` contacts.
When relay module is not powered, or is in bootloader mode, it is not energized (connects `NC` and `COM`).

9f194d9a-3f91-5ab2-b7ee-ae0a84511592.title: Random Number Generator
9f194d9a-3f91-5ab2-b7ee-ae0a84511592.description:
Generates random numbers using entropy sourced from physical processes.

This typically uses a cryptographical pseudo-random number generator (for example [Fortuna](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortuna_(PRNG)>)),
which is periodically re-seeded with entropy coming from some hardware source.

8fa9a8dd-a7cb-5578-9c46-2ec350af8c7e.title: Role Manager
8fa9a8dd-a7cb-5578-9c46-2ec350af8c7e.description: Assign roles to services on the Jacdac bus.

25be5d20-82c0-5cd3-a21a-80ca2918d0f7.title: ROS
25be5d20-82c0-5cd3-a21a-80ca2918d0f7.description: A ROS (Robot Operating System https://www.ros.org/) controller that can act as a broker for messages.

7acec4ca-c95a-500e-be5d-241f3e585e67.title: Rotary encoder
7acec4ca-c95a-500e-be5d-241f3e585e67.description: An incremental rotary encoder - converts angular motion of a shaft to digital signal.

692a8457-4394-5c79-bd06-9ae2e83e8781.title: Satellite Navigation System
692a8457-4394-5c79-bd06-9ae2e83e8781.description: A satellite-based navigation system like GPS, Gallileo, ...

a787031e-0b40-5de0-be4a-20da2076b1f1.title: Sensor Aggregator
a787031e-0b40-5de0-be4a-20da2076b1f1.description:
Aggregate data from multiple sensors into a single stream
(often used as input to machine learning models on the same device, see model runner service).

c5575060-59f4-5643-a523-d65b9b16748d.title: Serial
c5575060-59f4-5643-a523-d65b9b16748d.description:
An asynchronous serial communication service capable of sending and receiving buffers of data.
Settings default to 115200 baud 8N1.

dd611d4e-2dec-582a-bb74-92f57c9879f2.title: Servo
dd611d4e-2dec-582a-bb74-92f57c9879f2.description:
Servo is a small motor with arm that can be pointing at a specific direction.
Typically a servo angle is between 0° and 180° where 90° is the middle resting position.

The `min_pulse/max_pulse` may be read-only if the servo is permanently affixed to its Jacdac controller.

5e26a7da-8ac7-52ac-8432-25305681826b.title: Settings
5e26a7da-8ac7-52ac-8432-25305681826b.description: Non-volatile key-value storage interface for storing settings.

23d9e1f1-d1bb-5dff-be43-0a88c0c6e02d.title: 7-segment display
23d9e1f1-d1bb-5dff-be43-0a88c0c6e02d.description: A 7-segment numeric display, with one or more digits.

602525fa-a66e-5402-895e-4972cefedf07.title: Solenoid
602525fa-a66e-5402-895e-4972cefedf07.description: A push-pull solenoid is a type of relay that pulls a coil when activated.

ce7a4291-fe88-5414-b44a-ceb24253468e.title: Sound level
ce7a4291-fe88-5414-b44a-ceb24253468e.description: A sound level detector sensor, gives a relative indication of the sound level.

43c8183f-a285-5404-91cf-bd2e9a515059.description: A microphone that analyzes the sound specturm

752a5e64-0e79-5888-8310-a81ce6d1d770.title: Switch
752a5e64-0e79-5888-8310-a81ce6d1d770.description: A switch, which keeps its position.

e1f674c7-fca7-5e3a-9da0-2b1c516959b9.title: TCP
e1f674c7-fca7-5e3a-9da0-2b1c516959b9.description: Data transfer over TCP/IP and TLS stream sockets.

74ed19fb-b8b0-55f1-9360-39d9e3984967.title: Temperature
74ed19fb-b8b0-55f1-9360-39d9e3984967.description: A thermometer measuring outside or inside environment.

2bd6b558-cff0-5b9a-bdee-067374b9f397.description:
Supports aggregating timeseries data (especially sensor readings)
and sending them to a cloud/storage service.
Used in DeviceScript.

Note that `f64` values are not necessarily aligned.

3029416e-14a1-523c-932d-2b8e3885abca.title: Traffic Light
3029416e-14a1-523c-932d-2b8e3885abca.description: Controls a mini traffic with a red, orange and green LED.

b61447d9-0c59-561c-8812-f047a9535c0c.title: Total Volatile organic compound
b61447d9-0c59-561c-8812-f047a9535c0c.description: Measures equivalent Total Volatile Organic Compound levels.

32a56884-efa6-578b-afc0-bd66e69db811.title: Unique Brain
32a56884-efa6-578b-afc0-bd66e69db811.description:
The presence of this service indicates that this device is a client that controls sensors and actuators.
If a unique brain detects another younger unique brain (determined by reset counter in announce packets),
then the older brain should switch into proxy mode.

a4a61905-d18a-5228-88b6-76a94efa5d8c.title: USB Bridge
a4a61905-d18a-5228-88b6-76a94efa5d8c.description:
This service is normally not announced or otherwise exposed on the serial bus.
It is used to communicate with a USB-Jacdac bridge at the USB layer.
The host sends broadcast packets to this service to control the link layer.
The device responds with broadcast reports (no-one else does that).
These packets are not forwarded to the UART Jacdac line.

Packets are sent over USB Serial (CDC).
The host shall set the CDC to 1Mbaud 8N1
(even though in some cases the USB interface is connected directly to the MCU and line settings are
ignored).

The CDC line carries both Jacdac frames and serial logging output.
Jacdac frames have valid CRC and are framed by delimeter characters and possibly fragmented.

`0xFE` is used as a framing byte.
Note that bytes `0xF8`-`0xFF` are always invalid UTF-8.
`0xFF` occurs relatively often in Jacdac packets, so is not used for framing.

The following sequences are supported:

* `0xFE 0xF8` - literal 0xFE
* `0xFE 0xF9` - reserved; ignore
* `0xFE 0xFA` - indicates that some serial logs were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFB` - indicates that some Jacdac frames were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFC` - Jacdac frame start
* `0xFE 0xFD` - Jacdac frame end

0xFE followed by any other byte:
* in serial, should be treated as literal 0xFE (and the byte as itself, unless it's 0xFE)
* in frame data, should terminate the current frame fragment,
  and ideally have all data (incl. fragment start) in the current frame fragment treated as serial

613139c2-b22f-579f-a391-61e8029cdde7.description: The UV Index is a measure of the intensity of ultraviolet (UV) rays from the Sun.

e3fa829a-a427-5bd0-a30d-a5bd434f3f23.description: A mixin service that exposes verified telemetry information for a sensor (see https://github.com/Azure/Verified-Telemetry/tree/main/PnPModel).

9ba460fe-fb11-5ac8-9dc2-7b3b7c7a43d0.title: Water level
9ba460fe-fb11-5ac8-9dc2-7b3b7c7a43d0.description: A sensor that measures liquid/water level.

15e34665-7d66-5d1d-953a-a02b23ba37c5.title: WIFI
15e34665-7d66-5d1d-953a-a02b23ba37c5.description: Discovery and connection to WiFi networks. Separate TCP service can be used for data transfer.

c009d560-488b-533c-9d6d-3046d8078a0b.title: Wind direction
c009d560-488b-533c-9d6d-3046d8078a0b.description: A sensor that measures wind direction.

f1ad4ab2-716a-5984-b23c-a4c187be9371.title: Wind speed
f1ad4ab2-716a-5984-b23c-a4c187be9371.description: A sensor that measures wind speed.

88ddf30a-b004-5743-90c7-119cd231a80f.title: WSSK
88ddf30a-b004-5743-90c7-119cd231a80f.description:
Defines a binary protocol for IoT devices to talk to DeviceScript gateway over encrypted websockets.
This is not used as a regular Jacdac service.
